ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Well, odds are this is a course you'll be required to take if you're in the graduate program. But I think I would recommend it to astronomy students anyway, based on how well this particular professor presents and motivates the material.
A great introductions to observational astronomy in galaxies.
this course is a must take for anyone who wants to study galaxies in any capacity.
I think this would be a good course for any grad student in the department as it covers a lot of fundamentals of the topic of research on galaxies.
Learn all about galaxies. Do some math but mostly conceptual. Tough exams. Highly recommend.
I would recommend this course to anyone interested in galaxies

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I think this class was incredibly useful, and has helped tie together my "bigger picture" understanding of galaxies.
First class I took on galaxies. Learned a lot. Won't be very relevant to my thesis, but it's an important part of my mental picture of the universe.
